</p>
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Resource_item_arm  Entity: Resource_item  Attribute: resource_item 
   <express_ref linkend="resource_item:arm:Resource_item_arm.Resource_item.resource_item"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Resource_item_arm.Resource_item.resource_item">
<p>
A relationship to the item, type or actual, that is regarded as a resource within the application context.
</p>
<note number="1">
A resource can be a product, product category, product version, serialized product, person, etc.
</note>
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Resource_item_arm  Entity: Resource_item_relationship  
   <express_ref linkend="resource_item:arm:Resource_item_arm.Resource_item_relationship"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Resource_item_arm.Resource_item_relationship">
<p>
A relationship between two resource items. The role of the relationship is determined by classification.
</p>
<note number="1">
The relationship between a product and and a package could be classified as "Prefered".
</note>
</ext_description>
